        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 4:53PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 452 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Carrboro, or near Chapel Hill, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Raleigh, Durham, Cary, Chapel Hill, Garner, Carrboro, RDU
International, Apex, Morrisville, and Lake Wheeler.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
